Ford Motor Credit Company LLC Key Developments

Ford Motor Credit Company LLC to Report Q2, 2017 Results on Jul 26, 2017
Jul 12 17
Ford Motor Credit Company LLC announced that they will report Q2, 2017 results at 7:00 AM, US Eastern Standard Time on Jul 26, 2017


Ford Motor Credit Company LLC Issues and Sells $650,000,000 Aggregate Principal Amount of 2.425% Notes Due June 12, 2020
Jun 12 17
Ford Motor Credit Company LLC issued and sold $650,000,000 aggregate principal amount of 2.425% Notes due June 12, 2020 and $350,000,000 aggregate principal amount of Floating Rate Notes due June 12, 2020. The Debt Securities are to be issued pursuant to the provisions of an Indenture dated as of March 16, 2015 (the "Indenture"), between the Company and The Bank of New York Mellon, as Trustee. Pursuant to the terms of the Indenture, the company has created as a series of Debt Securities its 2.425% Notes due June 12, 2020 in the aggregate principal amount of $650,000,000 (the "2020 Notes"), and as a series of Debt Securities its Floating Rate Notes due June 12, 2020 in the aggregate principal amount of $350,000,000.


Ford Motor Credit Company LLC Reports Sales Results for the Month Ended April 2017
May 2 17
Ford Motor Credit Company LLC reported sales results for the month ended April 2017. For the month, the company reported overall U.S. sales for Ford were down 7.2% versus a year ago, with 314,695 vehicles sold. Retail sales totaled 140,765 vehicles, down 10.5%.


